\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532979\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532979\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vec1665702879448.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vec1665702879448.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vec1665702879448.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vec1665702879448\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Fallback Paths\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vec1665702879448__fallback_paths_98792\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface enables you to define alternative paths for executing remote components. In the client assignment file, you can use path-to-connector assignments to define a sequence of fallback paths to be used if the first path is not available. Interactive failures, such as incorrectly entering a user name or password, do not activate the fallback mechanism.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vec1665702879448__p_d30308e1_d30309e1_d30310e1\">If the initial path fails to open, an error is reported in the message frame and Uniface tries to open the first alternative path specified. If that path fails to open, an error is again reported and Uniface tries to open the second alternative path. This can be continued without a practical limit.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vec1665702879448__topic_d20192e1_d20193e1_d20194e1_d20195e1_d20196e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d695947e56\">\n                        \n Rules for Specifying Fallback Paths\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vec1665702879448__p_d30314e1_d30315e1_d30316e1\">To specify fallback assignments, follow these rules:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vec1665702879448__li_d15344e1_d15345e1_d15346e1\">Use only path-to-connector assignments. The target cannot be another path.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vec1665702879448__li_d15347e1_d15348e1_d15349e1\">Number each fallback assignment sequentially, beginning with 1. For example:\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"vec1665702879448__p_d30317e1_d30318e1_d30319e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[PATHS</code>]\n                             <var class=\"keyword varname\">$Path</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">= TCP:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Host</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">$Path</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[1] = TCP:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">HostOne</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">$Path</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[2] = TCP:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">HostTwo</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vec1665702879448__li_d15350e1_d15351e1_d15352e1\">Do not allow gaps in the numbering sequence.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vec1665702879448__p_d30320e1_d30321e1_d30322e1\">Errors are reported if these rules are not followed.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vec1665702879448__section_dq2_rgv_qcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d695947e133\">Example: Fallback Paths </h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">In the following example, two alternative paths are provided for the\n               path $SRU.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If the logon to node <code class=\"ph codeph\">phoenix</code> does not succeed,\n               Uniface tries to open the fallback path to <code class=\"ph codeph\">roc</code>. A Log On form is\n               presented for user <code class=\"ph codeph\">kaye</code> on node <code class=\"ph codeph\">roc</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If the user cannot log on to <code class=\"ph codeph\">roc</code> and clicks Cancel,\n               Uniface attempts to open the second fallback path. If that logon attempt also fails,\n               an error is reported to the process trying to open the path.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"vec1665702879448__pre_ng4_rgv_qcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$SRU = TCP:phoenix|kaye|birdbrain\n$SRU[1] = TCP:roc|kaye|?\n$SRU[2] = TCP:emu|general|?\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532979\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532979\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Fallback Paths Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Fallback Paths Uniface enables you to define alternative paths for executing remote components. In the client assignment file, you can use path-to-connector assignments to define a sequence of fallback paths to be used if the first path is not available. Interactive failures, such as incorrectly entering a user name or password, do not activate the fallback mechanism. If the initial path fails to open, an error is reported in the message frame and Uniface tries to open the first alternative path specified. If that path fails to open, an error is again reported and Uniface tries to open the second alternative path. This can be continued without a practical limit. Rules for Specifying Fallback Paths To specify fallback assignments, follow these rules: Use only path-to-connector assignments. The target cannot be another path. Number each fallback assignment sequentially, beginning with 1. For example: [PATHS ] $Path = TCP: Host | UserName | Password $Path [1] = TCP: HostOne | UserName | Password $Path [2] = TCP: HostTwo | UserName | Password Do not allow gaps in the numbering sequence. Errors are reported if these rules are not followed. Example: Fallback Paths In the following example, two alternative paths are provided for the path $SRU. If the logon to node phoenix does not succeed, Uniface tries to open the fallback path to roc . A Log On form is presented for user kaye on node roc . If the user cannot log on to roc and clicks Cancel, Uniface attempts to open the second fallback path. If that logon attempt also fails, an error is reported to the process trying to open the path. [PATHS] $SRU = TCP:phoenix|kaye|birdbrain $SRU[1] = TCP:roc|kaye|? $SRU[2] = TCP:emu|general|? Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}